                   order to explain the line profiles and the
                   position-velocity (PV) diagrams of C18O and SO
                   observed, simple models composed of an infalling
                   envelope surrounding a Keplerian disk of 54 AU in
                   radius orbiting a star of 0.3 M &sun; are examined.
                   It is found that in order to reproduce characteristic
                   features of the observed line profiles and PV
                   diagrams, the infall velocity in the model has to be
